.TH INSTALL_SYSTEMD_USER 1 "2026-06-09" "vscode-profile-importer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
install_systemd_user \- install example systemd user units for vscode-profile-importer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B install_systemd_user
\fI[--yes]\fP \fI[--user-dir DIR]\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR install_systemd_user
utility copies example systemd user service and timer units packaged with
vscode-profile-importer into the invoking user's
.BR ~/.config/systemd/user
directory and enables the example timer. The timer will run the example
service periodically to import a configured profile.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --yes
Assume yes for interactive prompts.
.TP
.B --user-dir DIR
Base user configuration directory (defaults to ~/.config).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Copy units and enable the timer for the current user (interactive):
.RS
.nf
install_systemd_user
.fi
.RE

.PP
Copy units and enable the timer non-interactively:
.RS
.nf
install_systemd_user --yes
.fi
.RE

.PP
After installing units, check the timer status:
.RS
.nf
systemctl --user status vscode-profile-importer-sync.timer
.fi
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Written by OpenCode.
